Looking at the balance sheet, I need to find the line item that represents the capital contributed by shareholders. 

In accounting, this is typically represented by "Paid-in Capital," which is the amount shareholders have invested in the company in exchange for shares.

- The "Paid-in Capital" end amount (as of 2024-02-05) is 28000000.00

This represents the capital contributed by shareholders, and it has remained unchanged during this period.
